Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.  When would you
use one instead of another?

    Forks - copy on git hub
    clones - copy on diffrent device
    branches - diffrent versions of work

    forks - us when colaborating with others
    clone - use to download for work on device
    branches - experiment/make major change

What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote
stored locally?

    Keep track of changes

